description.narrative: This programme component was largely dedicated to the pandemic response with significant achievements in improving quality of Primary Health Care (PHC) services and strengthening health system resilience while creating awareness onSARS-CoV-2transmission prevention and COVID-19 vaccination amongst the general population. Furthermore, major progress was made in the modelling of a community health model articulated around PHC centers, maternity waiting homes, and community relays with the completion of the inception phase and launch of the experimentation phase in selected underserved rural areas | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
